      "line": 56,
      "message": "with this approach, there's still way too much code here.  Let's try this:\n1) remove \"extends ...\"\n2) remove all methods except fromJson\n3) fromJson(Reader) uses a static gson object (with no type adapters) to read a JsonElement from the reader\n4) it then walks the JsonElement recursively (using the methods in the nested class below\n5) it then invokes: new StandardCoder().fromJson() to convert the JsonElement into the desired class\n6) remove \"extends...\" from the nested class below\n7) in the nested class, configure the crypto object in the constructor",
      "author": {
